Bachelor's Degree in Canada: Top Courses, Universities, Scholarship

  • 712 Reads
  • 3 min Read
  • By:CANAM Group

Planning to study for your preferred bachelor’s degree in Canada? Read the blog to know everything about universities available in Canada, top courses, fees, scholarship options, requirements, standardized English tests, and how to apply for Bachelor's Degree in Canada.

Studying in Canada is the dream of almost every student in India. The country has some of the top-ranked universities offering a range of programs. The scholarship opportunities, part-time work opportunities, and affordable education compared to other study-abroad destinations make studying in Canada more desirable for International students.

Studying in Canada after the 12th is one of the most rewarding decisions that a student can make. Canadian academic institutes offer a wide range of programs to help students gain mastery in their chosen field of study. Students can choose subjects like science, mathematics, humanities, history, and engineering. After studying bachelor's in Canada, students can access various job opportunities within the country.

Requirements for Bachelor's Degree in Canada for International Students

To check the academic eligibility of applicants, universities in Canada use GPA (Grade Point Average). International students planning to study in the country are required to have a minimum GPA score to apply for a bachelor's degree of their choice.

To take admission in a Bachelor's degree program in Canada, international students are required to take 60-70% marks in high school, but when it comes to bachelor's certificate/diploma, the cut-off is more flexible.

Standardized English Tests for Bachelor's Degrees in Canada

To study for a bachelor's degree in a Canadian university, non-native speakers are required to take English language proficiency test to showcase their knowledge and fluency in the language. Here are some of the tests accepted by universities in Canada:

IELTS

IELTS is one of the most popular English language proficiency tests that assesses any test taker on four parameters: Listening, Speaking, Reading, and Writing. Almost all universities/colleges accept the IELTS test for study in Canada. To study for a bachelor's degree in Canada, candidates must score a minimum IELTS band score of 6, but some colleges also ask for a 6.5 band score.

TOEFL(iBT)

TOEFL is also accepted by most of the universities and colleges in Canada. Test takers get the results of the exam within 6-8 days. To get admission to bachelor's degree program, students need a score between 80 and 100 in the test.

Pearson Test of English (PTE)

Numerous universities and colleges in Canada also accept PTE. This test is available for students in India who can get the results for this exam within 2-3 days.

Bachelor's Degree in Canada: Cost

Canada is one of the top affordable study-abroad destinations compared to other countries. The international student going to study Bachelor's Degree in Canada has to bear two expenses, i.e. the cost of living and tuition fees. The tuition fees for a bachelor's program in Canada depend on the kind of program and Institution you choose.

Bachelor’s Degree in Canada: Scholarships

Universities in Canada and the Government of Canada offer partially-funded and fully-funded scholarships to students planning to study in Canada. Connect with Counsellors at Canam to learn about the available scholarship options.

How to Apply for Bachelor's Degree in Canada

The universities in Canada give equal importance to practical and theoretical knowledge. In classes, students gain knowledge from seminars and projects as well, giving them access to unparalleled knowledge.
Studying in Canada gives students infinite opportunities to explore different career avenues and gain educational credentials that are respected all across the globe.

FAQ

How many years is a Bachelor's degree in Canada?

The Bachelor's degree in Canada is 3-4 years, which mainly depends on the chosen program. International students can study Bachelor's degree in Canada after completing their secondary schooling.

Which Bachelor's degree is the best in Canada?

Here are some of the top undergraduate courses that students can pursue in Canada:
•Business Studies and Finance
•Hotel Management
•Engineering
•Art and Design
•Construction Management
•Media Studies
•Computer Science
•Health

How much is the Bachelor's fee in Canada?

The fee for studying Bachelor's in Canada highly depends on the program and institution chosen by students. If you choose to study your preferred program in a top university in Canada, you will have to pay a lot more as compared to the other institute. You can go and check the official website of your desired university to confirm the fees.

Is an Indian bachelor' degree valid in Canada?

There are numerous Indian and overseas universities recognized by WES - World Education Services. The educational credentials gained from these universities are considered for – The educational Credentials Assessment.

Is bachelor’s 4 years in Canada?

Bachelor's degree in Canada is of 3-4 years. It mainly depends on the program a student opts for. To pursue a certain degree, students need to complete certain levels of education:

•For a bachelor's degree (3-4 years): a high school diploma
•For a master's degree (1-2 years): bachelor's degree

Is Canada cheaper for Indian students?

Education in Canada is considered one of the best in the world. Studying in Canada is comparatively more affordable than in other leading study-abroad destinations. The tuition-fee differs on the basis of the program/university any student chooses to apply for.
